review_text:
Stopped, dead;
Bad reaction, dead;
Blink, dead;
You don't know the map well, you're dead;
Not playing enough, you're dead;
Didn't have time to draw your weapon - dead;
Got a weapon and died;
You got hit by a skill, you die;
You don't know your skills, you're dead;
Did not follow the terrain and jumped out the wrong place - dead;
Can't shoot a jump shot - dead;
Can't hit a jumping man - dead;
60 hertz, dead;
240 hertz, dead;
Run the game, dead;
dead - dead.

There is very little variety when it comes down to it. Every run ends up feeling the same. It doesnt seem like the issues are a simple fix, either.

I was hoping it would be good :l

if you ignore the ip attached to this game, it becomes apparent how milquetoast and inferior it is compared to other similar titles :(
